Myroxylon balsamum var. perei.

   [7896.jpg]
    Authority   (L.) Har.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 7896

   Notes
   SOURCES (M. balsamum var. pereirae (Royle) Harms)
   Duke J 1981 pp 175-177 [FER, DRA, RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 319 [USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Evergreen perennial tree. Trees can be tapped for gum when 5-6 years
   old and can be tapped for 40-60 years or more.
   COMMON NAMES
   Peru balsam, Balsam of Peru.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: M. pereirae, Myrospermum pereirae, Toluifera
   Pereirae. Peru balsam is native to the west coats of Central America.
   It can grow up to 35 m tall. Found at altitudes up to 600 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
